Lenskart Air Grey Transparent Full Rim Square Eyeglasses are a stylish and functional eyewear choice that I have been thoroughly impressed with. The sleek design and transparent grey color of these glasses add a modern touch to any outfit, making them a fashion-forward accessory. The full rim square frame not only looks great but also offers durability, ensuring these glasses can withstand daily wear and tear.

One of the standout features of these eyeglasses is the clarity provided by the lenses. With exceptional lens quality, they offer a crystal-clear view, enhancing my vision and reducing eye strain. Whether I'm reading, working on my computer, or simply going about my daily activities, the Lenskart Air Grey Transparent eyeglasses provide a sharp and detailed visual experience. However, while I appreciate the overall design, I do have a slight doubt regarding the strength of the end piece that connects the temple to the frame. Although it appears sturdy, I can't help but wonder if it might become a potential weak point over time. It would be reassuring if Lenskart could address this concern and reinforce the end piece to ensure long-term durability.

Another consideration to note is that the temple length may be a little shorter for wider sizes. While the glasses fit comfortably on my face, individuals with broader facial structures might find the temple length slightly restrictive. A small adjustment to accommodate wider sizes would improve the overall fit and make these eyeglasses even more versatile for a wider range of customers. Despite these minor concerns, the Lenskart Air Grey Transparent Full Rim Square Eyeglasses are a fantastic choice for anyone looking for a stylish and reliable eyewear option that combines fashion and functionality.

I have been a regular customer of GKB and Titan Eye Plus and have been wearing corrective glasses for high myopia since times immemorial Although its only been a week since i got these glasses, i can say with certainty that the quality of Tokai Lutina lenses(Lenskarts premium product) is better than those provided by GKB Titan Eye Plus I used to opt for glass instead of CR39/Polycarbonate/Fibre because high index glass lenses come with an RI of 19 making them the thinnest in the world for people with high myopia However, i found Tokais Lutina lenses to be super thin for MY power in diopters They are made from a new material and contain lutein, a substance naturally found in the macula They come with a variety of coatings and do reduce the strain on eyes while looking at screens The only downside is that they arent as transparent as glass I got the package for Rs 13588 including Gold Membership and i think the price is competitive Great Product, great service and courteous staff

In 3 months, one of the glasses came off the frame.Eventually alignment of the temple became worse and I threw it away. Visited one of the lenskart outlets in my city and ordered two specs and the purchase was mind blowing!! Cheaper and 100 times durable than the previous one. Most importantly the showroom executives and technicians were super cool and understanding. It took around 45 mins to find the exact power of my eyes coz my eyes are a bit complicated. reviewTitle: Reviewing after a week of use
reviewDetail: Pros- 1- Very comfortable, No itching, No redness, 2- Wearable time 16-18 hours with comfort, can be extended till 20 hours, 3- Affordable and good quality lens with free solution, 4- I switched from Bausch and Lomb to Aqualens, Aqualens is easy to wear and provides moree comfort,,,,,,,,,,,,, Cons- 1- For beginners, it may get hard to wear these lenses as these are very soft but practicing once and twice will do the work, 2- Removing of lens become a tedious task for beginners as Aqualens want the lens to stay at your pupil without any discomfort, it sets properly, My personal recommendation would be, while putting out the lens from your eye, Slide it down a bit from pupil and just softly pinch it out, Conclusion - These lens are really good and very affordable and provides all day comfort, just use properly, clean it before wearing, Beginners dont hesitate, I took around 1 hr for both eyes on my very first experience, now just 1 min do it all

reviewTitle: Reviewing after a week of use
reviewDetail: Pros- 1- Very comfortable, No itching, No redness, 2- Wearable time 16-18 hours with comfort, can be extended till 20 hours, 3- Affordable and good quality lens with free solution, 4- I switched from Bausch and Lomb to Aqualens, Aqualens is easy to wear and provides moree comfort,,,,,,,,,,,,, Cons- 1- For beginners, it may get hard to wear these lenses as these are very soft but practicing once and twice will do the work, 2- Removing of lens become a tedious task for beginners as Aqualens want the lens to stay at your pupil without any discomfort, it sets properly, My personal recommendation would be, while putting out the lens from your eye, Slide it down a bit from pupil and just softly pinch it out, Conclusion - These lens are really good and very affordable and provides all day comfort, just use properly, clean it before wearing, Beginners dont hesitate, I took around 1 hr for both eyes on my very first experience, now just 1 min do it all

As a long time user of daily disposable lenses, I've found Aqualens to be the most comfortable. I switched to Aqualens around 1.5 years back starting with a free trial pack from Lenskart. I switched over from Aucuvue Moist which I'd been using for several years but though its thinner, it's harder to handle, and tends to dry out sooner and stick to the eyes if accidentally worn overnight or in the shower. In contrast Aqualens has a better performance. Though with prolonged use, I find that the wearing comfort longevity tends to decline. This may be true for all contacts, since the eyes need to breathe and therefore once or twice a week I wear spectacles. Btw also tried Focus dailies and B&L and found they didn't work for me.
Finally, I wish daily lenses are made more affordable esp for regular users as I do not want to consider corrective laser surgery.

reviewTitle: quick delivery and really comfortable lens
reviewDetail: This is the second time I’m ordering this daily disposable lens. And as a person with dry eyes I have to say that this is the most comfortable alternative to me than monthly lens. I feel like this lens is thinner than the regular lens so it was a bit difficult to put on as it folds every time I try to put it on. But once it’s on then it’s really comfortable to the eyes as it’s thinner. I used this for more than 12 hours a day for a function and then disposed it. But my eyes were still fine by the end of the day which is usually not the case with me. 100% recommend for people with dry eyes and who regularly get eye infections because of lens. Also appreciate lenskart for the quick delivery and amazing customer service. I usually order from WhatsApp after consulting with a customer care executive they helped me find this lens when I told them my concerns about dry eyes.

As a long time user of daily disposable lenses, I've found Aqualens to be the most comfortable. I switched to Aqualens around 1.5 years back starting with a free trial pack from Lenskart. I switched over from Aucuvue Moist which I'd been using for several years but though its thinner, it's harder to handle, and tends to dry out sooner and stick to the eyes if accidentally worn overnight or in the shower. In contrast Aqualens has a better performance. Though with prolonged use, I find that the wearing comfort longevity tends to decline. This may be true for all contacts, since the eyes need to breathe and therefore once or twice a week I wear spectacles. Btw also tried Focus dailies and B&L and found they didn't work for me.
Finally, I wish daily lenses are made more affordable esp for regular users as I do not want to consider corrective laser surgery.

Yearly Disposable Lens:-
These are those lens which has an expiry of a year.After the seal is opened,its life starts and recommendable dispose after a year.

Monthly Disposable Lens:-
These are those lens which has an expiry of a month.After the seal is opened,its life starts and recommendable dispose after a month.

Weekly Disposable Lens:-
These are those lens which has an expiry of a week. After the seal is opened,its life starts and recommendable dispose after a week.

Daily Disposable Lens:-
These are those lens which has an expiry of a day.After the seal is opened,its life starts and recommendable dispose after a day

Each contact lens comes with separate and fixed power .

It is surprising that Lenskart doesn't know about its products. I bought a pair of Bausch and Lomb B4 series contact lenses and got one box of B4 and the other U4 series box. Then I called the customer care and they asked me to return the product so that it could be replaced. After so much of investigation and procedures they told me that Lenskart does not deal in U4 series and I'll be sent the B4 soon. But to my amazement, the second time also the same U4 lens was delivered. After talking with so many customer care executives I decided to call official customer care of Bausch and Lomb where they explained me that from power -3.75 to -5.00 they have the U4 series. And from power -0.50 to -3.50 it's the B4 series. 
Just because of Lenskart being unaware I have been through such a hassle. 
P.S.- My power is -3.50 and -3.75

reviewTitle: quick delivery and really comfortable lens
reviewDetail: This is the second time I’m ordering this daily disposable lens. And as a person with dry eyes I have to say that this is the most comfortable alternative to me than monthly lens. I feel like this lens is thinner than the regular lens so it was a bit difficult to put on as it folds every time I try to put it on. But once it’s on then it’s really comfortable to the eyes as it’s thinner. I used this for more than 12 hours a day for a function and then disposed it. But my eyes were still fine by the end of the day which is usually not the case with me. 100% recommend for people with dry eyes and who regularly get eye infections because of lens. Also appreciate lenskart for the quick delivery and amazing customer service. I usually order from WhatsApp after consulting with a customer care executive they helped me find this lens when I told them my concerns about dry eyes.

reviewTitle: bid a farewell to all other lenses
reviewDetail: I have been using lenses since past 4 years. I saw these Moist Acuvue lenses on Lenskart and ordered them to give a try. I founded these lenses so comfortable that I bid a farewell to all other lenses. These lenses are extremely comfortable to wear. I had to be very overcautious with my early lenses that I do not take nap while wearing them but these one are like a blessing. I can work on computer for hours without facing any redness are irritation and at times I can even take a nap. These lenses have a water holding technology which provides a comfort throughout the wearing. With the 15 per cent discount offered by Lenskart, I was so pleased that I ordered packs for two months.

These contact lenses are worth money spent.
- These are daily disposable
- No need to clean them, simply use and throw
- Best option for those prone to eye allergies
- Can be worn for hours without any tension
- Discounted price with Lenskart
- Water holding ingredient that moistens the eyes
- A fresh and smudge free experience.
Negative points: a bit expensive
Other thoughts: very comfortable and justify every penny spent

reviewTitle: Prompt service; Product Quality as hoped for
reviewDetail:
I asked for a home eye test for my mother, as she can't step out during these covid times, with the idea that I could get new lenses for her nice set of frames. I was told that the lens only replacement service has been suspended during the covid period. Didn't understand why. The home testing was very well done, with maintaining all hygiene. The service professional was excellent at his job and very patient. 
A reasonable collection of frames were shown. However, the ones we initially chose were not available once it was checked for online. That was slightly disappointing. We chose certain alternatives. The lens was to be bi-focal. Since my mother uses her phone and tablet a lot, we thought we would get the blue coating. But I was told that for bifocal lens, that feature was not available. Again, I didn't understand why. Again, slightly disappointing. But resigning to the otherwise convenient service, and the otherwise good reputation of Lenksart, decided to order two glasses. Both were delivered within the time indicated. The glasses were of prime quality - good fit, light on the nose. the box was nice. So, here's a customer more satisfied than not, primarily because of the incredible convenience in this all. Despite lack of some product availability, service quality was outstanding.

reviewTitle: Unnatural so uncomfortable initially but decent after a few days
reviewDetail: The lens is good. Since its an unnatural thing to put, the initial 4-5 times it feels horrible. I felt cheated with all the positive reviews but after talking to a friend who uses them I was relieved. Try putting them on 4-5 days in a row even if it's for 1 min. You'll feel very uncomfortable the first day and probably will not even be able to put it on in the first 20-30 attempts but slowly you'll catch on. 2nd day I was able to get it on in 10 attempts. 3rd in 5 attempts and 4th day onwards 3-4 attempts and that's how many attempts it still takes. Now it doesn't hurt anymore

reviewTitle: Classy looks but crap build quality
reviewDetail:
This is a long term review. Posting this after 7 months of the buying date.
Pros:
•The thin rims and thin side frame makes the specs stand out from the ordinary especially being black
•It being circular in design makes you have a wider and longer view
•the silicon nose grip is a massive W as it never slips out of the nose (unless you're sweaty)
Cons:
• The biggest highlight of the con is the build quality
• The paint of the top and bottom of the lens frame chipped off after just over a month from sitting on a surface when removed, exposing the steel primer colour
• The nose grip is very flimsy and as a result one broke off in two pieces. 
• the rear end of the frame behind the ear is too long and crosses well beyond my hair. When laid back on a sofa, the specs pushes forward and i have to adjust it frequently
• To be honest this has been very uncomfortable and frustrating experience for me. But kudos to lenskart team for replacing this item without any hassle.

Talking about my old review, it got deleted by the team since I can't even see it now to update. Hence I'm writing a new one.

First I got NAG lenses which are not good in any way. They get smudges easily and their glare levels are so high that I was feeling great discomfort wearing them. 
Now I exchanged them for Blu lenses and there's improvement in these. Though there's still a little glare in green colour which is natural. 
What shocked me is Anti glare lenses in lenskart are equivalent to NAG lenses in Vasan eye care. Though they both cost almost same (with lenskart offer). 

Other points worth noting is that
The hinges move smoothly. They don't have self closing or self opening ability towards ends while pushing. 
Quality looks really premium except for the hinge movement.
A silver colour variant would really be an overkill.

Also the customer care team are really helpful before and after sales. 

Verdict: Buy the glasses only if you opt for Blu lenses. Else don't
